== Parameters ==

=== Required parameters ===

All required parameters are determined by position only&mdash;there is no name (e.g. no <tt>name=value</tt> form) associated with a required parameter.

;{{tl|Golf18}}
:No required parameters.

;{{tl|Par18}}
:The par for holes 1&ndash;9, followed by the par for the front 9, followed by the par for holes 10&ndash;18, followed by the par for the back 9, followed by the par for all 18 holes.  (21 parameters)

;{{tl|Handicap18}}
:The hole handicap for holes 1&ndash;18. Note that hole handicaps are assigned with all of the odd numbers from 1&ndash;18 assigned to holes 1&ndash;9 and all of the even numbers assigned to holes 10&ndash;18.  (18 parameters)

;{{tl|Tee18}}
:The name of the tee (e.g. '''Regular''' or '''Blue'''), followed by the slope/rating, followed by the yardages for holes 1&ndash;9, followed by the yardage for the front 9, followed by the yardages for holes 10&ndash;18, followed by the yardage for the back 9, followed by the yardage for all 18 holes.

;{{tl|Black18}} {{tl|Blue18}} {{tl|White18}} {{tl|Yellow18}} {{tl|Red18}} {{tl|Green18}} {{tl|Gold18}} {{tl|Silver18}}
:The slope/rating, followed by the yardages for holes 1&ndash;9, followed by the yardage for the front 9, followed by the yardages for holes 10&ndash;18, followed by the yardage for the back 9, followed by the yardage for all 18 holes.

=== Optional parameters ===

All of the optional parameters are named&mdash;they use the form <tt>name=value</tt>. The templates support the following optional parameters:

;bcolor  (all templates)
:Overrides the default background color. Example: <tt>bcolor=red</tt>

;tcolor  (all templates)
:Overrides the default text color. Note that when used with {{tl|Golf18}}, this also sets the default text color for any {{tl|Par18}} and {{tl|Handicap18}} templates in the scorecard. Example: <tt>tcolor=white</tt>

;rssize  (all templates)
:Overrides the size of the font used to display the rating/slope. When used with {{tl|Golf18}}, this overrides the size of the font in the rating/slope column heading. Note that for {{tl|Par18}} and {{tl|Handicap18}}, there is no rating/slope text unless the optional '''name''' parameter is also provided. Examples: <tt>rssize=8pt</tt> or <tt>rssize=smallest</tt>

;name  ({{tl|Black18}}, {{tl|Blue18}}, {{tl|White18}}, {{tl|Yellow18}}, {{tl|Red18}}, {{tl|Green18}}, {{tl|Gold18}}, and {{tl|Silver18}})
:Overrides the default name of the tee.  (The default name is the name of the tee color.)  Example: <tt>name=Championship</tt>

;name  ({{tl|Par18}} and {{tl|Handicap18}})
:Provides a name in the rating/slope column to identify either the tee or whether the par/handicap is for men or women. Example: <tt>name=Womens</tt>

;title  ({{tl|Golf18}})
:The table caption displayed centered over the top of the scorecard. If not specified then no title is displayed. Example: <tt>title=South Course</tt>

;center  ({{tl|Golf18}})
:A boolean parameter&mdash;if set to a non-empty value, then the table is centered horizontally on the page. Example: <tt>center=true</tt>

